		<section id="applicability">
			<h2>When to Use</h2>
			<p class="instructions">This technique can be used when the purpose of the form field can be determined from the HTML type element and the context of the page. The most common example of this is password and user name forms where there are only two form fields, and the information entered is about the end user and the page title is login.</p>
		</section>
